        {
            "word": "apologize",
            "wordType": "verb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To say you are sorry for something you have done wrong or for a mistake that caused "
                },
                {
                    "text": "harm or inconvenience",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "someone else",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "يَعتذر",
            "synonyms": [
                "say sorry",
                "express regret",
                "make amends"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "He immediately "
                },
                {
                    "text": "apologized",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " when he realized he had taken his roommate's lunch from the refrigerator by mistake"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "American spelling: apologize. British spelling: apologise. Pattern: apologize to someone FOR something ('apologize to her for being late'). NOT 'apologize about' (less common)."
        },
        {
            "word": "assure",
            "wordType": "verb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To tell someone confidently that something is true or will happen to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "remove their doubts",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " or "
                },
                {
                    "text": "fears",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "يُطمئن / يؤكد",
            "synonyms": [
                "guarantee",
                "promise confidently",
                "reassure"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "The airline representative "
                },
                {
                    "text": "assured",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " us that our delayed luggage would arrive by morning"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "NOT the same as 'ensure' (to make certain something happens) or 'insure' (financial protection). Pattern: assure someone THAT... or assure someone OF something."
        },
        {
